OL,6,FThe relatively smooth journey of this
OL,7,Fbudget will be seen as a win for John
OL,8,FSwinney and a triumph for the politics
OL,9,Fof collaboration and compromise so
OL,10,Foften absent at Holyrood.
OL,12,FAs the leader of a minority government
OL,13,Fthe First Minister was always going to
OL,14,Fneed to make a deal with at least one
OL,15,Fother party to get his tax and
OL,16,Fspending plans through. From the off
OL,17,Fhe emphasised the need for parties to
OL,18,Fwork together and appealed to the
OL,19,Fother leaders to work with him in what
OL,20,Fhe's described as difficult economic
OL,21,Fcircumstances.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G4/9
